rComments: As a lecturer he's actually good but the department screwed him by the dropping the course on him with little noticeprep time . He did what he could with what he had and was passionate;  most people would've flipped out under the pressure and bc half the students were self-entitled idiots who were there bc they heard the course was an easy-A.

He's a nice instructor who tries to be helpful and will answer all questions and provide all help if you need. It is unfortunate that due to some issues beyond his control (TAs being lame, him getting pushed into teaching this course out of the blue without much prior warning), the courses ended up being quite messy. That said, he knows his stuff..

He's a pretty nice guy if you ever go talk to him after lectureduring office hour. He's speedy to responding to my emails, and I've been sending him quite a few. The course could use some organization, but I recently learned it was his first time teaching, so that's understandable. I think the course will be much better the next time he teach it.

It's December and we have ZERO assignments back, of which the first two were identical in the material they were testing and the third was textbook questions. Does not do enough in class examples, and the ones he gets to he doesn't finish or are overly simple

The material was easy, but you had to figure out what he was saying first. Class examples were full of errors, he said he would post examples and slides, but often the slides were useless and examples were posted late. The course is almost over and we haven't gotten any assignment marks. The book is good, but optional, so matching material is hard.
IF YOU HAVE HIM, DROP THE CLASS.
